Ask HN: Have we reached ChatGPT article saturation yet?
text:
Have a look at the current front page. It's been a couple days at least that ChatGPT and AI articles have filled at least 1/3rd of it.

Lisp on here is cyclical, arrives like a comet, showers us with articles about it, and leaves for months at a time. It's always a lovely sight.

We have had the Erlang days, that were so bad pg had to personally intervene.

Then there was the Bitcoin phase, and that also required a divine hand to stop it from getting out of hand.

Now it's another AI hype era, both in Computer Science and on this site. Have we reached maximum ChatGPT hype yet? For something so technologically advanced yet accessible to anyone, there awaits us a massive pile of written word on it for the foreseeable future, and personally, I have started to tune it out.

title: Ask HN: Tools for Visualising Baysian Networks?
text:
I've searched high and low but can't find a link previously submitted to HN: It was a really neat visual tool to make Bayesian calculations from a DAG.

The user entered priors for various quantities, and for the correlation between them, and the interface would show a conditional posterior distribution... it was a way of quickly simulating a range of outcomes given non-point estimates for contributing variables. I think it was all written in JS – the UI was quite slick.

If anyone can remember what this was would be incredibly grateful!

Ask HN: I want to train a LM on my home country's dialect, how can I do it?
text:
I'm from Algeria. The language spoken on a daily basis by almost everybody is a weird mix of different languages : french, arabic, english..etc.

I was thinking of grabbing data from tweets to fine-tune the model. I may be able to figure out other sources, but it's not gonna be much better than that. Just short-form text for the most part.

I was thinking of potentially leveraging the smaller models I came across recently (nanoGPT for example) or something similar.

I'm tech-savvy enough to make this work but I'd like some feedback from people more knowledgeable than me before I spend time and effort into this.

Thanks!
